Which part of the following URI is the path?


https://CatalystCenter.example.com/dna/intent/api/v1/interface/network-device?/1/1/5

&nbsp;

explanation:
&nbsp;

	There are six required attributes for REST APIs, including these two attributes:


		Client/server architecture: REST APIs operate in the client/server model. This means that an application is built with RESTful APIs that act as the server. A client computer or device would make a RESTful API call to the application.

		Layered system: With REST APIs, you can leverage the single URI to complete any task at hand. In the background you have no idea that the URI you used actually ended up utilizing several servers/services in the back end.


	Additionally, note that while JSON data can be transferred over a REST API, REST does not require the use of JSON.&nbsp;

The key:value pair that has a numeric value is &ldquo;lastUpdateTime&quot;: 1572317520439. To realize this fact, you can look for values not enclosed in quotes, as JSON requires quotes around string values, but requires the absence of quotes around numeric values.

	As for the incorrect options, altough they all have numbers for their values, the incorrect answers are shown in the JSON text enclosed in quotes, so the values are strings.&nbsp;

	Note: This output is directly from a DNA Center RESTful API request called &ldquo;Get Network Device by IP&rdquo; and the output is in JSON form.

